Column Comment.0: INFORMATION ITEM SUBTYPE: the type of information item. May be one of Thevalid types of Information item as defined by check constraints.
Column Comment.1: INFORMATION ITEM ID: Unique identifier for the information item.
Column Comment.2: QUALITYE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the record describing a qualitycharacteristic of the information item.
Column Comment.3: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.4: ATTRIBUTE ACCURACY: a code for the attribute accuracy as defined by the metadata standard.
Column Comment.5: ATTRIBUTE ACCURACY DESCRIPTION: An explanation of the accuracy of theidentification of the entities and assignments of values in the data set and adescription of the tests used.
Column Comment.6: COMPLETENESS DESCRIPTION: A narrative description of the completeness ofthis information item. Information aobut omissons, selction criteria, generlaization,definitions used and other rules used to generate this dataset.
Column Comment.7: MAINTENANCE DUE DATE: the date when the next maintenance event is due.
Column Comment.8: DEFICIENCY INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating that this quality measure has adeficiency associated with it.
Column Comment.9: DEFICIENCY TYPE: The type of deficiency that has been found.
Column Comment.10: DESCRIBED BY BUSINESS ASSOCIATE ID: Validated business associate id for theBUSINESS ASSOCIATE who conducted or was responsible for identifying thisquality measure.
Column Comment.11: DESCRIPTION: A narrative description of the quality of the information item.
Column Comment.12: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.13: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.14: INFORMATION ITEM QUALITY CODE: A code indicating the quality of theinformation contained on the information item.
Column Comment.15: INFORMATION or ATTRIBUTE QUALITY DESCRIPTION: Narrative descriptivecomments about the quality of the information or attributes of this information item.
Column Comment.16: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should becreated.
Column Comment.17: QUALITY DATE: the date that this quality measure was recorded. For the range ofdates that this quality was in effect, please use effective and expiry dates.
Column Comment.18: REMARK: Narrative remarks relating to this row of data.
Column Comment.19: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.20: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.21: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.22: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.23: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.24: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.25: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.26: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
